UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. Strengthened national capacity to deliver improved health and nutrition outcomes for children, adolescents, pregnant women and other vulnerable groups and contribute to sustained improvements in population dynamics

description.narrative: UNICEF support to the development of a Regulatory Impact Assessment for the draft National Nutrition Policy and the integration of the District Nutrition Action Plans in the District Development Plans in 18 focus districts contributed to further strengthening the enabling environment for nutrition. At service delivery level, as a result of UNICEF support, 8,153,838 children aged 6–59 months received vitamin A supplementation and 30,794 children aged 6–59 months were treated for severe acute malnutrition. COVID-19 accentuated the underlying and immediate causes of child undernutrition, including inadequate diets, sub-optimal health services, poor childcare practices and food insecurity. | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
